# Roasted Winter Salad

> Colorful #salad dish for the dark winter days for a useful entree or side

## Roasting Beets

> Save your large roasting dish for the later step in this recipe. Make sure to set up the oven to fit your large roaster as well.

Preheat oven to 425Â°F

- Beets | 1 bunch, with greens | Chop step about 1/2 inch (reserve for later), washed

Lay beats in baking dish and fill 1/4 inch water into baking dish

Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 35 minutes

## Roasting Squash

> Use a large roasting tray here for the squash.

Line roaster with aluminum foil

- Squash | 2 lbs | Peeled, sliced 1/2 inch
- Olive Oil | 2 tbsp | 

Toss with some salt

Bake for 25 minutes, turn at half-way

## Preparing the Salad

> Meanwhile, prepare the remaining salad ingredients

Bring large water pot to boil

Cook beet greens 1 minute

Drain and rinse with cold water

Chop course

## Dressing

- Balsamic Vinegar | 1 tsp | 
- Garlic | 1 clove | Minced or pressed
- Olive Oil | 2-3 tbsp | 
- Walnut Oil | 2 tbsp | 

De-skin beets, slice tops, then in half, then into half-moon

Split dressing in half, toss beets and squash separately

## Serving

Arrange in alternating rows on individual plates

- Walnuts | 1.5 oz or 3 tbsp | Chopped
- Herbs (Parsley, Mint, Tarragon, etc.) | Any, 2 tbsp | 

Add toppings, and opt. Feta cheese

